cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper is about deep learning-based robotic grasping. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the paper involves using sensor inputs of a scene to estimate the probability of success of a grasp. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper involves training a deep neural network for grasp planning. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper involves developing an autoregressive grasp planning model. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper involves developing a model for controlling robotic grasping.
